xdi2.messaging.target.impl
Class CompoundMessagingTarget

java.lang.Object
  xdi2.messaging.target.impl.AbstractMessagingTarget
      xdi2.messaging.target.impl.CompoundMessagingTarget
All Implemented Interfaces:
MessagingTarget
public class CompoundMessagingTarget
extends AbstractMessagingTarget

A messaging target that can combine multiple other messaging targets. Incoming messages will be sequentially applied to all individual targets, and a single message result will be produced.

Author:
markus

public boolean execute(Operation operation,
                       MessageResult messageResult,
                       ExecutionContext executionContext)
                throws Xdi2MessagingException
We execute an operation by letting all our individual messaging targets execute it.

Overrides:
execute in class AbstractMessagingTarget
Parameters:
operation - The XDI operation.
messageResult - The result produced by executing the message envelope.
executionContext - An "execution context" object that is created when execution of the message envelope begins and that will be passed into every execute() method.
Returns:
True, if the operation has been handled.
